rComments: Really kind guy, charasmatic slightly, but still unique enough to keep you attentive. EASY CLASS, EASY SLIDES, AND COOL ATMOSPHERE. He tends to regrade and grade fairly and is always just a nice guy. Kudos

He's so friendly and he honestly cares about you as a student. His class is an easy A, if you pay attention. I didn't need the textbook, all the information you need is in his slides (which he sometimes posts and other times does not).He gives easy bonus questions on tests and his outline is super clear so if you don't do well thats on you.

Very fair professor, make sure you go to class and take notes as he does not post slides. I found the textbook helpful. The midterms are multiple choice and very easy. There's also an essay worth a huge part of your grade. He's so nice he gave us the questions for the final exam in advance.

Fantastic professor. Respectful in his conversations with students and incredibly amicable -- I found him approachable and really helpful with my work. It's really a shame that he doesn't teach more courses at uOttawa because he's one of my preferred PAP Professors.

I really enjoyed the class, I thought it was well organized. He was clear and his slides followed the textbook very closely. If you went to class and paid attention you will be able to do well. Midterms were just multiple choice, exam was fair. He gave a list of potential questions/what to study ahead of time. Very approachable.

Very approachable prof. He likes his topic and is very knowledgeable. His classes are stimulating because he poses questions and comments to the class in a non-condescending way. His requirements and feedback for assignments and exams are very clear. Take a course with him.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: a lot of readings. test was ok. it'd be helpful if he posted slides online. still a good prof.
fun prof, answers questions quickly. textbooks are xpensive tho.
Third year student and never had him before, really funny in class and seems to like teaching.
